5000|$|Allspice, {{also called}} pimenta, <b>Jamaica</b> pimenta, myrtle <b>pepper,</b> Turkish yenibahar, is the dried unripe fruit (berries, {{used as a}} spice) of Pimenta dioica, a midcanopy tree native to the Greater Antilles, {{southern}} Mexico, and Central America, now cultivated in many warm parts of the world. The name [...] "allspice" [...] was coined as early as 1621 by the English, who thought it combined the flavour of cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves.|$|R
